Description:

Small Union Square based Architectural practice seeks junior architect to join the firm.

Office specializes in the analysis and restoration of existing buildings and the preservation of historic structures.  We have a commitment to high-quality work, an insistence on proper detailing and a strong regard for longevity.

Projects range from one-room historic structures to five-hundred unit residential buildings, and from the rehabilitation of tenement buildings to the restoration of some of the most prestigious buildings in the city.  Projects are based in NYC.


Qualifications:
Be conscientious and enthusiastic & meticulous;
Have initiative and self-motivation;
Have experience in the preparation of construction documents;
Have excellent drafting skills and the ability to produce hand sketches on-site;
Be highly proficient in Vectorworks and be familiar with MS Office programs;
Have a Bachelor of Architecture;
Have keen interest or experience in historic preservation & exterior restoration;
Have desire to learn and enthusiasm;
Be unafraid of heights and be willing to get hands dirty.


Email resume with limited portfolio excerpts only where relevant to items above.


Long Island City studio of di Domenico + Partners, a midsized NYC Architecture/Landscape Architecture Design firm, seeks:

Junior Architect: 3+ years of experience
The primary duties of the Junior Architect will be to provide project participation in all phases of design including Concept Design, Design Development, Construction Documents and Construction Administration. The candidate will be expected to understand and develop aspects of working drawings and details. The following is required of the candidate:

• Bachelors or Masters degree in Architecture (professional degree only);
• 3+ years of experience;
• Proficiency in AutoCAD 2014 or later, with BIM (Revit) project experience a plus;
• Experience with Adobe Suite and rendering programs (3D Max or Rhino are preferred);
• Experience with Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint)

Preferred project experience includes K-12 schools, higher-education projects, design of large-scale public projects (transit stations, convention centers, and similar).

Experience and interest in sustainable design/documentation/LEED is strongly encouraged, with applicable accreditations preferred.

Email resumes and examples of work to reply address indicated above.

di Domenico + Partners, LLP is an equal opportunity employer. The firm offers full benefits including health insurance, dental and vision insurance, 401K matching, and profit sharing.


